onsecutive season in the top flight of Scottish football and the third in the newly established [[Scottish Premiership]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11781/8838339/new-spfl-branding-is-unveiled | title=New SPFL branding is unveiled | publisher=[[SKY Sports]] | work=skysports.com | date=24 July 2013 | accessdate=24 July 2013}}</ref> having been promoted from the [[Scottish First Division]] at the end of the [[1984\u201385 Scottish First Division|1984\u201385 season]]. Motherwell will also compete in the [[2015\u201316 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] and the [[2015\u201316 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]].\n\n==Important Events==\nOn 12 June 2015, Motherwell announced their first batch of Pre-season Friendlies.<ref>{{cite web|title=First pre-season games announced|url=http://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2015/06/12/first-pre-season-games-announced/|website=motherwellfc.co.uk/|publisher=Motherwell|accessdate=19 June 2015|date=12 June 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 September 2015, Motherwell parted ways with manager [[Ian Baraclough]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Club Statement: Ian Baraclough|url=http://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2015/09/23/club-statement-ian-baraclough/|website=motherwellfc.co.uk/|publisher=Motherwell FC|accessdate=23 September 2015|date=23 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 October 2015, [[Mark McGhee]] returned to the club as manager.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34511651 |title=Motherwell name Mark McGhee as manager for second spell |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=13 October 2015 |accessdate=13 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Mark McGhee returns as Motherwell boss|url=http://www.motherwellfc.co.uk/2015/10/13/mark-mcghee-returns-as-motherwell-boss/|website=www.motherwellfc.co.uk|publisher=Motherwell F.C.|accessdate=13 October 2015|date=13 October 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Results & Fixtures==\n{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffcccc|Los