tern_b1    = _thinwhitehoops\n| pattern_ra1   = _whitehoops\n| pattern_sh1   = \n| pattern_so1   = \n| leftarm1      = FF0000\n| body1         = FF0000\n| rightarm1     = FF0000\n| shorts1       = FFFFFF\n| socks1        = FFFFFF\n<!-- Away kit -->\n| pattern_la2   = _black_stripes\n| pattern_b2    = _blackstripes\n| pattern_ra2   = _black_stripes\n| pattern_sh2   = \n| pattern_so2   = \n| leftarm2      = 0000FF\n| body2         = 0000FF\n| rightarm2     = 0000FF\n| shorts2       = 000000\n| socks2        = FFFFFF\n| prevseason = [[2013\u201314 Hamilton Academical F.C. season|2013\u201314]]\n| nextseason = [[2015\u201316 Hamilton Academical F.C. season|2015\u201316]]\n}}\n\nThe [[2014\u201315 in Scottish football|2014\u201315 season]] was [[Hamilton Academical F.C.|Hamilton Academical's]] first season in the top flight of Scottish football since [[2010\u201311 Scottish Premier League|2010-11 season]], and their first in the newly established [[2014\u201315 Scottish Premiership|Scottish Premiership]] having been promoted from the [[2013\u201314 Scottish Championship]] through the [[2013\u201314 Scottish Premiership#Final|Play-offs]]. Hamilton also competed in the [[2014\u201315 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] and the [[2014\u201315 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]].\n\n==Summary==\n===Management===\nThe club began the 2014-15 season under the management of [[Alex Neil (footballer)|Alex Neil]]. On 9 January 2015, Neil left to become the new manager of, at the time, [[Football League Championship|English Championship]] side [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30744801|title=Alex Neil: Norwich City appoint Hamilton player-manager as boss|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|work=bbc.co.uk/sport|date=9 January 2015|accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref> [[Martin Canning]] was appointed Caretaker Player-manager, and was later on 23 January 2015 officially appointed Player-manager.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30937644|title=Hamilton Academical: Martin Canning becomes new manager|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|work=bbc.co.uk/sport|date=23 January 2015|accessdate=22 February 2015}}</ref> With top goalscorer [[Tony Andreu]] also leaving,<ref>{{cite news|title=Transfer Deadline Day: Norwich City sign Tony Andreu|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31104649|publisher=BBC|date=4 February 2015 |accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref> the club suffered with the sudden departures and Canning had to wait 14 matches for his first victory as manager, coming on 24 April 2015 in the [[Lanarkshire derby]] at home to [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32346135|title=Hamilton Academical 2-0 Motherwell|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|work=bbc.co.uk/sport|date=24 April 2015|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffcccc|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#cccccc|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Pre-season===\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|nobars = y\n|date = 9 July 2014\n|time =19:45\n|round = Friendly\n|score = 1 \u2013 0\n|report =[http://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/sport/football/hearts/robbie-neilson-not-worried-by-lacklustre-display-in-hamilton-1-3472660 Evening News Report]<br />[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/hamilton-1-hearts-0-3837892 Daily Record Report]<br />[http://www.scotsman.com/sport/football/spfl/hamilton-accies-1-0-hearts-gillespie-wins-it-1-3472063 Scotsman Report]\n|team1 = Hamilton Academical\n|team2 = [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]]\n|goals1 =[[Grant Gillespie (footballer)|Gillespie]] {{goal|90+1}}\n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[New Douglas Park]], [[Hamilton, South Lanarkshire|Hamilton]]\n|attendance = 883\n|referee = Andrew Dallas\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|nobars = y\n|date = 15 July 2014\n|time =19:45\n|r