on || Edinburgh City ||align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n|}\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{Reflist|group=nb}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://pfascotland.co.uk/ The official website of the Professional Footballers' Association Scotland]\n\n{{Scottish football awards}}\n\n[[Category:Scottish football trophies and awards]]\n[[Category:Awards established in 2007]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Professional Footballers' Association Scotland Team of the Year''' (often called the '''PFA Scotland Team of the Year''', or simply the '''Team of the Year''') is an annual award given to a set of 44 footballers in the four national tiers of the [[Scottish football league system]], who are seen to be deserving of being named in a \"Team of the Year\". The award is compiled by the members of the players' [[trade union]], [[Professional Footballers' Association Scotland]] (PFA Scotland), with the winners then being voted for by the other players in their respective divisions.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/football/four-celtic-players-make-team-of-year.20980691 |title=Four Celtic players make team of year |work=The Herald |publisher=Herald & Times Group |date=3 May 2013 |accessdate=3 May 2013}}</ref> The award was instituted in the [[2006\u201307 in Scottish football|2006\u201307]] season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/4940144.stm |first=Colin |last=Moffat |title=SPL: team of the season |work= |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 April 2006 |accessdate=3 May 2013}}</ref><ref name = \"2007 award\">{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/scotland/6584145.stm |title=SPFA's team of the 2006/07 season  |first=David |last=Sharp |work= |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 April 2007 |accessdate=3 May 2013}}</ref> In that first season, the award was voted for by the [[manager (association football)|managers]] in each division.<ref name = \"2007 award\"/>\n\n==Key==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Positions{{#tag:ref|For more info