ing Group|Headline]] |location= |isbn=0755361067 |page=740 |pages= |url=}}</ref>\n | stadium       = [[Victoria Park, Dingwall|Victoria Park]]\n | league        = [[2009\u201310 Scottish First Division|First Division]]\n | league result = '''Fifth place'''\n | cup1          = [[2009\u201310 Scottish Challenge Cup#Semi-finals|Challenge Cup]]\n | cup1 result   = '''Semi-final''', lost to [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]]\n | cup2          = [[2009\u201310 Scottish League Cup#Third round|League Cup]]\n | cup2 result   = '''Third round''', lost to [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n | cup3          = [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup#Final round|Scottish Cup]]\n | cup3 result   = '''Final''', lost to [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n | league topscorer   = <br>[[Richard Brittain]] (9)\n | season topscorer   = <br>[[Michael Gardyne]] (13)\n | highest attendance = 5,928 vs. [[Inverness Caledonian Thistle F.C.|Inverness Caledonian Thistle]], 20 March 2010<ref name=\"First\">{{cite web | url=https://int.soccerway.com/national/scotland/first-division/2009-2010/regular-season/ | title=First Division 2009/2010 | publisher=Soccerway | accessdate=26 July 2012}}</ref><!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n | lowest attendance  = 1,752 vs. [[Greenock Morton F.C.|Greenock Morton]], 8 December 2009<ref name = \"First\"/><!--LEAGUE ONLY-->\n | average attendance = 2,465<ref>{{cite book |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2010-11 |last1=Rollin |first1=Glenda |last2=Rollin |first2=Jack |year=2010 |publisher=[[Headline Publishing Group|Headline]] |location= |isbn=0755361067 |pages=761 |url=}}</ref>\n | prevseason = [[2008\u201309 Ross County F.C. season|2008\u201309]]\n | nextseason = [[2010\u201311 Ross County F.C. season|2010\u201311]]\n}}\n\nThe [[2009\u201310 in Scottish football|2009\u201310 season]] was [[Ross County F.C.|Ross County's]] second consecutive season in the [[2009\u201310 Scottish First Division|Scottish First Division]], having been promoted as champions of the [[Scottish Second Division]] at the end of [[2007\u201308 in Scottish football|2007\u201308 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://scottish-football-historical-archive.com/promotionrelegation.htm |title=Scottish Football League & Scottish Premier League |publisher=Scottish Football Historical Archive |accessdate=26 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929152050/http://scottish-football-historical-archive.com/promotionrelegation.htm |archivedate=29 September 2012 }}</ref> They also competed in the [[2009\u201310 Scottish Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]], [[2009\u201310 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], and [[2009\u201310 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]].\n\n==Summary==\nRoss County finished fifth in the [[Scottish First Division|First Division]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/tables/_/league/sco.2/season/2009/scottish-division-one?cc=5739# | title=2009/10 Scottish Division One Table / Table | publisher=[[ESPN]] | work=ESPN Soccernet | accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref> They did, however, reach the semi-finals of the [[Scottish Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/challenge-cup/results/3197926/ | title=Inverness Caledonian Thistle  1\u20130  Ross County | publisher=[[Scottish Football League]] | work=scottishfootballleague.com | date=4 October 2009 | accessdate=27 July 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120814050822/http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/challenge-cup/results/3197926/ | archive-date=2012-08-14 | url-status=dead }}</ref>  and the third round of the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/league-cup/results/3191974/ | title=Ross County  0 - 2  Dundee United | publisher=[[Scottish Football League]] | work=scottishfootballleague.com | date=22 September 2009 | accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref> They also managed to gain entrance into the final round of the [[Scottish Cup]],<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/scottish_cup_fixture_details.cfm?page=1988&matchID=97382 | title=Ross County F.C. v Dundee United F.C. | publisher=[[Scottish Football Association]] | work=scottishfa.co.uk | date=15 May 2012 | accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref> but lost to [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_cups/8682861.stm | title=Dundee Utd   3 - 0   Ross County | publisher=BBC | work=BBC Sport | date=15 May 2012 | accessdate=27 July 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.rosscounty-mad.co.uk/results_fixtures/2009_2010/ross_county/index.shtml | title=Ross County's results from season 2009/2010 | publisher=County Mad | accessdate=26 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/first/results/archive/2009-2010/ | title=First Division Results 2009/2010 | publisher=[[Scottish Football League]] | date=16 May 2010 | accessdate=26 July 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100722203920/http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/first/results/archive/2009-2010 | archive-date=22 July 2010 | url-status=dead | df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/challenge-cup/results/archive/2009-2010/ | title=Challenge Cup 2009/10 | publisher=[[Scottish Football League]] | date=22 November 2009 | accessdate=26 July 2012 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110106001557/http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/challenge-cup/results/archive/2009-2010/ | archive-date=6 January 2011 | url-status=dead | df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.scottishfootballleague.com/football/league-cup/results/archive/2009-2010/ | title=Scottish Communities League Cup Results 2009/2010 | publisher=[[Scottish Football League]] | date=21 March 2010 | accessdate=26 July 2012}}</ref>{{legend2|#ccffcc|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#ffffcc|Draw